text:
Some more details on your options...
• Easter Island: a few large, inanimate, frowning faces made of stone on a single, mostly treeless, very remote, patch of ground.
• Galapagos Islands: multiple beautiful islands filled with hundreds of endemic species that don't exist anywhere else in the world, including giant tortoises (up to 900 lbs, 4'3'' long) :turtle:, marine iguanas (basically just small godzillas) :lizard:, lava lizards :volcano:, flightless cormorants :eagle:, blue-footed boobys :bird:, and tropical penguins:penguin:(the only penguins in the northern hemisphere :dancing-penguin:). Also dolphins :dolphin:, sharks :shark:, coral :coral:, and snorkeling :diving_mask:. And it's the #3 destination in Central/South America (<https://travel.usnews.com/rankings/best-central-and-south-american-vacations/>)!!!
